"{\"uid\": \"newsweek.com-donald-trump-takes-credit-la-2028-olympics-1937666\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Published  Aug 12, 2024 at 02:31 AM EDT  updated  Aug 12, 2024 at 08:24 AM EDT  US News Reporter  Former President Donald Trump has claimed credit for securing Los Angeles as the host city for the 2028Olympics, in a late-night Truth Social post on Sunday.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 255, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 80, \"end\": 87, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/U.S._News_&_World_Report\", \"score\": 0.999571164971914, \"rank\": 0.0002925128413137053, \"text\": \"US News\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/U.S._News_&_World_Report\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/U.S._News_&_World_Report\"}, {\"begin\": 115, \"end\": 127, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999242438438662, \"rank\": 7.576024341637414e-05, \"text\": \"Donald Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}, {\"begin\": 160, \"end\": 171, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999359913565, \"rank\": 6.171706509677086e-08, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 227, \"end\": 239, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Truth_Social\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Truth Social\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Truth_Social\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Truth_Social\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"As President-Elect, I worked with the Olympic Organizing Committee of Los Angeles in getting the 2028 Olympics to come to the United States.\", \"from\": 257, \"to\": 398, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 328, \"end\": 339, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999359913565, \"rank\": 6.171706509677086e-08, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 384, \"end\": 397, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999341083412088, \"rank\": 6.589598886023002e-05, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There was tremendous competition from other countries,\\\" he wrote.\", \"from\": 399, \"to\": 464, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Los Angeles had initially been competing with Paris to host this year's Olympics.\", \"from\": 466, \"to\": 547, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 466, \"end\": 477, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999359913565, \"rank\": 6.171706509677086e-08, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 512, \"end\": 517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999998267833384, \"rank\": 1.7321662569947456e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2017, Trumpput his weight behind the city's bid, but the Olympic Organizing Committee awarded Paris hosting rights for 2024 and Los Angeles rights for 2028.\", \"from\": 548, \"to\": 707, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 645, \"end\": 650, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999998267833384, \"rank\": 1.7321662569947456e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In his Truth Social post Trump also accused former PresidentBarack Obamaof not being supportive of the bid.\", \"from\": 709, \"to\": 816, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 716, \"end\": 728, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Truth_Social\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Truth Social\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Truth_Social\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Truth_Social\"}, {\"begin\": 734, \"end\": 739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9998355192566833, \"rank\": 0.0001643926049094751, \"text\": \"Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"President Obama refused to speak to the International Olympic Committee (perhaps because of a previous rejection by them of a proposal personally made by him!\", \"from\": 818, \"to\": 977, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 819, \"end\": 834, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barack_Obama\", \"score\": 0.9999999374936144, \"rank\": 6.250637898794667e-08, \"text\": \"President Obama\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barack_Obama\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barack_Obama\"}, {\"begin\": 859, \"end\": 890, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"), which needed the enthusiastic support and approval of the U.S. President - Without which they would not have chosen our Country.\\\"\", \"from\": 977, \"to\": 1109, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Trump met with Thomas Bach, the president of the International Olympic Committee at the White House in June 2017.\", \"from\": 1111, \"to\": 1224, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1126, \"end\": 1137, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thomas Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\"}, {\"begin\": 1160, \"end\": 1191, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Obama did not meet IOC representatives at the White House butdid attend an IOC session in Copenhagen in 2009to back Chicago's ultimately unsuccessful bid for the 2016 Games.\", \"from\": 1226, \"to\": 1399, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1226, \"end\": 1231, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barack_Obama\", \"score\": 0.9999998911009756, \"rank\": 1.0870011760586945e-07, \"text\": \"Obama\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barack_Obama\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barack_Obama\"}, {\"begin\": 1245, \"end\": 1248, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2741324431707822e-21, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1316, \"end\": 1326, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Copenhagen\", \"score\": 0.9999592304757732, \"rank\": 3.9032461200737474e-05, \"text\": \"Copenhagen\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Copenhagen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Copenhagen\"}, {\"begin\": 1342, \"end\": 1349, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\", \"score\": 0.9999173966981365, \"rank\": 8.256993673165501e-05, \"text\": \"Chicago\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Obama's personal pitch to the IOC for Chicago was rejected and the organizers gave hosting rights to the Brazilian city of Rio de Janeiro instead.\", \"from\": 1401, \"to\": 1547, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1401, \"end\": 1406, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barack_Obama\", \"score\": 0.9999998911009756, \"rank\": 1.0870011760586945e-07, \"text\": \"Obama\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barack_Obama\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barack_Obama\"}, {\"begin\": 1431, \"end\": 1434, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2741324431707822e-21, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1439, \"end\": 1446, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\", \"score\": 0.9999173966981365, \"rank\": 8.256993673165501e-05, \"text\": \"Chicago\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\"}, {\"begin\": 1524, \"end\": 1538, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"score\": 0.9997513140939283, \"rank\": 0.00024874776611775974, \"text\": \"Rio de Janeiro\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Trump concluded by writing that, if elected as president in November, he would bring the same approach to deal-making that secured the Olympics to making the country successful.\", \"from\": 1549, \"to\": 1726, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1549, \"end\": 1554, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9998355192566833, \"rank\": 0.0001643926049094751, \"text\": \"Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I gave them what they wanted to hear, and got the job done!\\\"\", \"from\": 1728, \"to\": 1789, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"he said.\", \"from\": 1790, \"to\": 1798, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was my great honor to do so.\", \"from\": 1799, \"to\": 1831, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hopefully I will be President, and our Country will have reached new (and record!)\", \"from\": 1832, \"to\": 1914, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"levels of success.\", \"from\": 1915, \"to\": 1933, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"SEE YOU IN 2028.\", \"from\": 1934, \"to\": 1950, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thank you!\\\"\", \"from\": 1951, \"to\": 1962, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was one of several posts theRepublicanpresidential candidate posted on Truth Social Sunday night.\", \"from\": 1964, \"to\": 2064, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2038, \"end\": 2050, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Truth_Social\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Truth Social\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Truth_Social\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Truth_Social\"}]}, {\"s